				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twisting Songs<a name="68595"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 31 04 9:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Your best bet is to use the guides posted to get information like this.  I will give you a quick answer though.  A song has its effects going for 3 ticks (18 seconds) after it is started.  Every song has a 3 second cast time, which means between 3 and 4 songs can be going at once if you start a different song right as you finishing singing one.  
<br />

<br />
This is called twisting.  So you start a song, wait three secs for the cast time, when it finishes, stop playing it, then start another.  Do this until you get your 3rd or 4th song up, then go back to the first.  In this way, you get multiple songs going at once.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
