			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twisting Songs<a name="68605"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 1 04 6:08 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;A song has its effects going for 3 ticks (18 seconds) after it is started. Every song has a 3 second cast time, which means between 3 and 4 songs can be going at once if you start a different song right as you finishing singing one.&quot;
<br />

<br />
Just to be picky... 8-)
<br />

<br />
In actual fact, a song's effect is only up for 2 ticks (12 seconds), which is why you can only twist 4 (with no missed notes, so reliably 3).
<br />

<br />
Everyone *says* they last 3 ticks (18 seconds), and that's the info Lucy etc pulled out of the spell files, however if they lasted 18 with a 3 second cast we'd be able to twist up to 6 (18 / 3 = 6).
<br />

<br />
I've tested this extensively with a stopwatch (yes, I'm sad!), and for all our regular 'buff' songs that put an icon in the song box the icon is there for 12 seconds.
<br />

<br />
So, just dispelling a common myth there 8-)
<br />

<br />
Katawarl, and her stopwatch</span></td>
