				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twisting Songs<a name="68661"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 1 04 12:38 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Actually the icon and the buff last for 3 server ticks landing, not a fixed duration in seconds, which is 12.1-17.9 seconds variable. (using .1 arbitrarily, I suppose you could use .01, .00 etc)
<br />

<br />
Thats why you  can have 3 songs with a four second cast time up continuously (assuming no stuns, even with a few missed notes) but why the 4 song twist (assuming it is all 3 tick songs) even under perfect conditions will drop, with out fail, at some point.
<br />

<br />
To say it a different way, when you cast you get the icon when the song lands, as do most party members, regardless of server tick, the next server tick will land some where between .1 and 5.9 seconds after the song lands, and will continue for 12 more seconds (two more additional 6 second ticks)...giving you the duration above.
<br />

<br />
The effects such as mana, damage, to the best of my knowledge only get applied for 3 server ticks regardless, but buff/debuff benefits, I believe, last for the length of the icon duration. It should be noted that icons sometimes drop for party members at different times, which I assume is server/client communications differences?
<br />

<br />
In additions, I have seen arguments for the 5 song targetted dot  which assume a full 18 second duration, meaning that you could possibley get the damage to land 4 times, if the song duration fell at the right time. Whether or not those folks have empirical evidence to back that up, I don't know.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
