				<td colspan="2"><span>Twisting is something we just have to do if we want to keep several effects going. You can leave bellow running, but you can also sing haste, regen, bellow. When you're meleeing toe-to-toe mobs often bash you. That will interrupt any song casting and you will have to start the song again.
<br />

<br />
It may seem a big deal, but once you get used to it, the finger movement on twisting will become automated. I tried to twist my warrior's kick-taunt-disarm keys after a while of playing just my bard. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
Being female and blonde shouldn't hinder you, there's lots of us and we are just as good bards as anyone else. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /></span></td>
