			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twisting Songs<a name="68998"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 4 04 4:16 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Think of it as juggling.  You have to toss the ball up for it to go into the air.  But once it's up in the air you don't have to do anything until it's going to fall, so you catch it and toss it back up.  So next you need to toss up a second ball for it to be considered juggling.  So you toss up one ball, grab another and toss it up, the first falls, but you catch it and toss it back up, the second falls, so you catch it as well and toss IT back up.  Now you are juggling.  Toss in a third ball and it's a little harder to keep all three balls up in the air at once, but it <b>IS</b> doable.  Some people can manage a fourth ball and they are just <b>stupendous jugglers</b>!
<br />

<br />
The casting bar = tossing up the ball
<br />
The icon disappears = the ball falling to the ground before you caught it.
<br />
Starting a different song = tossing up another ball
<br />

<br />
Good luck, dear...  &lt;warm hugs&gt;</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
