			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twisting Songs<a name="69236"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 8 04 1:16 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">In additions, I have seen arguments for the 5 song targetted dot which assume a full 18 second duration, meaning that you could possibley get the damage to land 4 times, if the song duration fell at the right time.</span></blockquote>
<br />
Not entirely, this still assumes a 3-tick duration and 3x damage per dot. The trick behind doing more than 4 dots is exactly what you mentioned earlier, namely that mana and damage etc. are applied on server ticks, and not when a song lands (this is true for DoT's but not for DD's btw.). Here's how it works:
<br />

<br />
Let's assume 6 dots, labelled A, B, C, D, E, F. Let's also assume that you start casting the first dot 1 second before a server tick (call this t=-1, with the tick at t=0).
<br />

<br />
T=-1: start A
<br />
<b>T= 0: Tick 0</b>
<br />
T= 2: finish A, start B
<br />
T= 5: finish B, start C
<br />
<b>T= 6: Tick 1</b> A, B do damage
<br />
T= 8: finish C, start D
<br />
T=11: finish D, start E
<br />
<b>T=12: Tick 2</b> A, B, C, D, do damage
<br />
T=14: finish E, start F
<br />
T=17: finish F, restart A
<br />
<b>T=18: Tick 3</b> A,B,C,D,E,F do damage. A,B wear off.
<br />
T=20: finish A, restart B
<br />
T=23: finish B, restart C
<br />
<b>T=24: Tick 4</b> C D E F A B do damage, C,D wear off
<br />
T=26: finish C, restart D
<br />
T=29: finish D, restart E
<br />
<b>T=30: Tick 5</b> E,F,A,B,C,D do damage, E,F wear off
<br />
T=32: finish E, restart F
<br />
T=35: finish F, restart A
<br />
<b>T=36: Tick 6</b> A,B,C,D,E,F do damage. A,B wear off.
<br />
T=38: finish A, restart B
<br />
T=41: finish B, restart C
<br />

<br />
...etc...
<br />

<br />
Caveat: this scheme assumes perfect timing on the twists, no missed notes, and no resists. So in reality some dots will miss a tick or a cycle occasionally. With the right low-resist mobs it's doable to do 5 quite consistently though.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Aeryon,
70 Rock Legend on Brell</span></td>
