				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twisting Songs<a name="69298"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 9 04 8:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Playing a Bard is somewhat more difficult than the other classes.  At least, playing one well...
<br />

<br />
Twisting is work, and when doing it you almost can't communicate with the other players.  It can be hard to move around, so repositioning yourself in melee because the pets are shoving the mob along is a nuisance.
<br />

<br />
You are pretty much *constantly* casting.  As soon as one song is cast, start the next.  Pick three songs and keep singing them over and over.  That's Twisting.  When you get good at it, you can try twisting more than three.
<br />

<br />
One thing I find helpful is to have hotkeys for my song gems.  I have 8 of them.  Each one is set up the same:
<br />

<br />
/stopsong
<br />
/cast 1
<br />

<br />
Or cast 2, or 3, one for each gem.  Using that cuts my button-pushing needs in half.</span></td>
